narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Start off with quantum mechanics, atomic bonding, electrical properties, thermodynamics, surface tension, diffusion, and defects of a crystal. Final project presentation at the end of the course on a topic of your choice. Midterm and final exam. Sporadic psets. I would recommend this course.
I would recommend taking it. No other class gets as in depth to small devices as this class. Professor Reed's class is much more generalized, but this class gets more specific.
The workload is less/same as compared to other classes at YaleGood choice for elective
The class is infinitely more interesting in the second half of the course, and Prof Han is a good lecturer.
